Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones. Pop them into a #mixing bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @mayonnaise{64%g} and toss to coat. In another small #bowl{}, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} with half the @Central American style spice mix{2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and stir in the @oil for the breadcrumbs{1%tbsp}.

Add the spicy crumbs to the florets and toss to coat evenly.

Pop the crumbed florets onto a lined #baking tray{} and spread them out in a single layer. Discard any leftover crumbs in the bowl.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Spicy Bean Stew ==

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}, deseed and finely chop.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

> MOD: If you've chosen to add chorizo to your meal, add to the frying pan at the same time as the courgette.

Once hot, add the courgette and cook, stirring, for ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and remaining Central American style spice mix and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%can} and @water for the sauce{75%ml}. Bring to a simmer, then bubble away for ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Transfer a third to a bowl and crush with a #fork{}.

After 5 mins, add the whole and crushed beans to the stew. Cook until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir half the coriander into the stew, then remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and as much red chilli as you'd like (add less if you don't like heat).

== Assembly ==

When the nuggets are crispy, remove from the oven.

Spoon the spicy bean stew into #bowls{}, then top with the cauliflower nuggets, @chorizo{60%g}(sliced) and a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}.

Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining coriander. Enjoy!